body:
<!-- Describe the issue -->
I attempted to import a private key to a new wallet.  After the rescan process i received a message of "null".
When i attempted to restart the program, the application it gives the following error message,
"Error: Cannot parse configuration file: parse error on line 1: importprivkey <My private key is in these brackets>"

<!--- What behavior did you expect? -->
I expected the application to run.

<!--- What was the actual behavior (provide screenshots if the issue is GUI-related)? -->
![Screen Shot 2020-01-18 at 6 56 35 PM](https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/35384463/72672185-830b2200-3a24-11ea-8168-040eae797c4b.png)

<!--- How reliably can you reproduce the issue, what are the steps to do so? -->
The error can be reproduced 100% of the time when attempting to open the application

<!-- What version of Bitcoin Core are you using, where did you get it (website, self-compiled, etc)? -->
The version of Bitcoin Core is 0.19.0.1.  The version was downloaded from https://bitcoin.org/en/bitcoin-core/.

<!-- What type of machine are you observing the error on (OS/CPU and disk type)? -->
Macbook Pro 15-inch mid 2012 -  MacOS Mojave V10.14.6

<!-- GUI-related issue? What is your operating system and its version? If Linux, what is your desktop environment and graphical shell? -->

<!-- Any extra information that might be useful in the debugging process. -->
<!--- This is normally the contents of a `debug.log` or `config.log` file. Raw text or a link to a pastebin type site are preferred. -->

I am sorry if this issue is a simple one.  I am relatively new to using this application.  I would appreciate any help possible.
title: Bitcoin Core Does not start
